				                <div>Hello chandru,<br />
<br />
Thank you for your question. By default, POP only downloads the INBOX and not the other folders including the "Sent."<br />
<br />
Since you are connecting from several locations (Webmail, Windows Live Mail, and phone), I recommend setting them all up as IMAP. This will allow all devices to see the same emails, since they are stored on the server.<br />
<br />
You can <a href="http://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/edu/cpanel/cpanel-email/creating-an-email-forwarder-in-cpanel">create Forwarders</a> in cPanel, or webmail at any time. <br />
<br />
But, it may be better to use a client such as Windows Live mail to connect to the individual accounts. You can then manage all the emails in one location.<br />
<br />
Thank you,<br />
John-Paul</div>
