				                <div>Hello Hal,<br />
<br />
This all depends on where your DNS is being controlled and how the mail is being set.  In general, if you change the A record for the domain and you want to KEEP your mail from an existing service, then you need to make sure that the mail setting in the DNS is pointing to the correct IP  as an A record and not a CNAME. It is typically set to a CNAME, but to keep mail service, it would need to be changed to an A record that is pointing to the right mail server.<br />
<br />
I hope this helps to answer your question, please let us know if you require any further  assistance.<br />
<br />
Regards,<br />
Arnel C.<br />
<br />
